criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          1. are 18+ years old;

          2. meet criteria for opioid use disorders of at least moderate severity (4 or 5 DSM-V
             criteria);

          3. Are currently taking medication-assisted treatment (MAT) as part of their standard
             clinical care;

          4. have no acute medical problem requiring immediate inpatient treatment;

          5. have no history of psychotic disorders, though those with other co-morbid
             psychopathology (mood disorders, anxiety, other substance use disorders) will be
             eligible;

          6. are willing to participate in a randomized clinical trial;

          7. provide the name, verified telephone number, and address of at least 2 contacts
             willing to help locate the patient, if necessary, during follow-up;

          8. are able to read and write in English;

          9. are not pregnant;

         10. are willing to share health-related data with primary care clinicians; and

         11. are, at study intake, abstinent from opioids for at least 1 week and no longer than 2
             months, except for medications used to treat the disorder (e.g., methadone).
